const homeDesc='Practical Indian wedding planning guides, Hindu ceremony explainers, regional traditions, invitation wording and a free wedding budget calculator.';
const homeBody=`<section class="home-hero"><div class="hero-copy"><p class="eyebrow">Indian wedding planning, made calmer</p><h1>Your Indian Wedding,<br><em>Beautifully Planned</em></h1><p>Clear, culturally respectful guidance for planning a celebration that feels true to your family—from the first guest-list conversation to the final vidaai.</p><form class="site-search" role="search" data-search><label class="sr-only" for="home-search">Search ShaadiGuide</label><input id="home-search" type="search" placeholder="Search ceremonies, checklists, invitations…" autocomplete="off"><button type="submit">Search</button><div class="search-results" hidden></div></form><div class="hero-actions"><a class="button" href="wedding-planning.html">Start Planning</a><a class="button secondary" href="wedding-budget-calculator.html">Calculate Your Budget</a></div></div><div class="hero-art" aria-hidden="true"><div class="mandala"><span>शुभ</span><small>विवाह</small></div><div class="arch"></div></div></section>${ad()}<section class="section"><div class="section-head"><div><p class="eyebrow">A thoughtful place to begin</p><h2>Plan every part of your celebration</h2></div><p>From practical decisions to meaningful traditions, find guidance you can adapt—not rules you must follow.</p></div>${cards([['Wedding Planning','Timelines, checklists and family responsibility ideas for a well-organised celebration.','wedding-planning.html'],['Hindu Ceremonies','Understand the meaning and flow of commonly observed wedding rituals.','hindu-wedding-ceremonies.html'],['Regional Weddings','Explore introductions to wedding traditions across India.','regional-weddings.html'],['Budget Tools','Build a clear estimate and see where your wedding budget is going.','wedding-budget-calculator.html'],['Invitation Wording','Original wording for traditional, modern and digital invitations.','invitation-wording.html'],['Our Editorial Promise','See how we approach accuracy, sensitivity and cultural variation.','editorial-policy.html']])}</section><section class="section tint"><div class="section-head"><div><p class="eyebrow">Popular ceremony guides</p><h2>Celebrate with understanding</h2></div><a href="hindu-wedding-ceremonies.html">View all ceremonies →</a></div><div class="feature-grid"><a href="haldi-ceremony.html" class="feature-card haldi"><span>Pre-wedding ceremony</span><h3>Haldi</h3><p>A joyful gathering centred on blessings, turmeric and family warmth.</p></a><a href="mehndi-ceremony.html" class="feature-card mehndi"><span>Pre-wedding celebration</span><h3>Mehndi</h3><p>Plan comfortable seating, artist timing, music and refreshments.</p></a><a href="hindu-wedding-ceremonies.html" class="feature-card ceremony"><span>Wedding-day rituals</span><h3>Pheras & Saptapadi</h3><p>Learn why sequence and interpretation differ across communities.</p></a></div></section><section class="section timeline-home"><div class="section-head"><div><p class="eyebrow">A calmer countdown</p><h2>Your wedding planning timeline</h2></div><a href="wedding-planning.html">Open the complete checklist →</a></div><ol class="timeline"><li><b>12 months</b><span>Align on priorities, budget range, guest estimate and possible locations.</span></li><li><b>9 months</b><span>Confirm key venues and high-priority vendors; begin attire research.</span></li><li><b>6 months</b><span>Plan invitations, ceremony logistics, décor direction and guest travel.</span></li><li><b>3 months</b><span>Finalise menus, schedules, fittings, music and family responsibilities.</span></li><li><b>30 days</b><span>Confirm numbers, payments, transport and your wedding-week run sheet.</span></li></ol></section>${ad()}<section class="section dark-section"><div class="section-head"><div><p class="eyebrow">Across India</p><h2>Regional traditions, respectfully introduced</h2></div><a href="regional-weddings.html">Explore regional weddings →</a></div><div class="region-row">${['Punjabi','Gujarati','Bengali','Marathi','Tamil','Telugu'].map(x=>`<a href="regional-weddings.html#${x.toLowerCase()}">${x}<span>Explore →</span></a>`).join('')}</div><p class="variation-note">Practices vary by locality, community and family. Our introductions are starting points for conversations with the people who know your traditions best.</p></section><section class="section split-section"><div><p class="eyebrow">Free planning tools</p><h2>Turn big questions into clear next steps</h2><p>Estimate costs in Indian rupees, see a category breakdown and print a summary for your family planning conversation.</p><a class="button" href="wedding-budget-calculator.html">Try the Budget Calculator</a></div><div class="mini-budget" aria-hidden="true"><span>Estimated celebration</span><strong>₹24,50,000</strong><div><i style="width:34%"></i><i style="width:25%"></i><i style="width:19%"></i><i style="width:22%"></i></div><small>Venue · Catering · Attire · Other</small></div></section><section class="section invitation-band"><div><p class="eyebrow">Words for a meaningful beginning</p><h2>Invitation wording for every kind of celebration</h2><p>Find original examples for formal cards, warm WhatsApp messages, reception-only invitations and thoughtful no-gifts notes.</p><a href="invitation-wording.html">Browse invitation examples →</a></div></section><section class="section"><div class="section-head"><div><p class="eyebrow">Latest guides</p><h2>Useful reads for your planning list</h2></div></div>${cards([['How to plan your Haldi','Create a comfortable, joyful event with practical ideas for timing, clothing, food and photography.','haldi-ceremony.html'],['A better Mehndi timeline','Give artists enough time while keeping guests comfortable and the celebration flowing.','mehndi-ceremony.html'],['The first five decisions','Start with priorities, budget, guest range, location and the format of your celebration.','wedding-planning.html']])}</section><section class="newsletter"><div><p class="eyebrow">Planning notes, coming soon</p><h2>Good advice for the months ahead</h2><p>Our email planning notes are not active yet. Bookmark ShaadiGuide and return as new guides and printable resources are added.</p></div><div class="newsletter-faux" aria-label="Newsletter preview"><input type="email" placeholder="Email updates coming soon" disabled><button disabled>Join later</button></div></section>`;
write('index.html',layout({file:'index.html',title:'ShaadiGuide | Indian Wedding Planning & Hindu Ceremony Guides',desc:homeDesc,h1:'Your Indian Wedding, Beautifully Planned',body:createPhase1BHome({ad,faqs}),type:'home',schemas:[{'@context':'https://schema.org','@type':'WebSite',name:'ShaadiGuide',url:site,description:homeDesc,publisher:{'@type':'Organization',name:'ShaadiGuide',url:site}},faqSchema(homeFAQs)]}));

const planFaq=[['When should we start planning an Indian wedding?','Many families begin 9 to 12 months ahead, especially for a multi-event celebration or popular season. A shorter timeline can work when priorities, guest numbers and decision-makers are clear.'],['Who should decide the wedding budget?','The people contributing financially should agree on a comfortable limit, what it includes and who approves changes. Keep this conversation private, specific and free from comparison.'],['How can families divide responsibilities?','Assign one accountable lead for each area—such as guest travel, ceremonies, venue coordination or payments—and keep a shared contact list and deadline tracker.'],['Do we need every traditional event?','No. Include ceremonies and celebrations that are meaningful, practical and agreed by your families. Confirm religious requirements with your priest, pandit or officiant.']];
const planContent=`${crumbs([['Wedding Planning']])}${intro('The complete starting point','Indian Wedding Planning Guide','A practical timeline for bringing families, ceremonies, guests and vendors together without losing sight of what matters to you.')} ${article(`<p class="article-lead">Indian weddings can include several events, many decision-makers and guests travelling from different places. Good planning does not mean making the celebration impersonal; it creates the space to be present.</p><h2>Begin with five major decisions</h2>${cards([['1. Shared priorities','Each partner names three must-haves and three areas where they can be flexible.'],['2. Comfortable budget','Agree on a total range, contributors, approval process and contingency.'],['3. Guest estimate','Create a realistic range before looking at venues or catering.'],['4. Place and season','Consider travel, weather, availability, accessibility and family needs.'],['5. Celebration format','Choose the events and approximate number of days before booking.']])}<h2>A 12-month planning timeline</h2><h3>12 months before: set the foundation</h3>${check(['Hold a calm priorities and budget conversation.','Draft the guest list by family group and identify uncertain invitations.','Shortlist the city, dates or date range; consult your officiant for religious requirements.','Visit venues and compare what each quotation includes.','Create one shared planning folder and a decision log.'])}<h3>9 months before: secure the essentials</h3>${check(['Confirm venue terms, deposits, access hours and cancellation conditions.','Book priority vendors such as planner, caterer, photographer and key entertainment.','Begin attire research, especially if custom work is planned.','Identify travel and accommodation needs for close family and older guests.','Outline each event and its likely guest count.'])}<h3>6 months before: shape the guest experience</h3>${check(['Finalise ceremony and reception formats with both families.','Choose the invitation direction and collect accurate names and addresses.','Develop décor, menu and music briefs tied to your budget.','Plan transport routes and accessibility support.','Review legal marriage requirements separately with the relevant authority.'])}<h3>3 months before: turn plans into schedules</h3>${check(['Send invitations according to guest travel needs.','Complete menu tastings and attire fittings.','Confirm ceremony items with the priest, pandit or officiant.','Build event-by-event run sheets with vendor arrival times.','Assign family contacts so the couple is not handling logistics on the day.'])}<h3>Final 30 days: confirm, do not reinvent</h3>${check(['Collect RSVPs and dietary or accessibility notes.','Give final counts only after checking contract deadlines.','Confirm outstanding balances and use traceable payment records.','Prepare seating, transport, rooming and emergency contact lists.','Pack documents, attire, jewellery and ceremony items by event.'])}${ad()}<h3>Wedding-week checklist</h3>${check(['Share the final run sheet and contact list with family leads and vendors.','Check weather and adjust only practical details.','Confirm who holds rings, documents, payments and emergency supplies.','Allow time for meals, hydration, rest and private moments.','Nominate one person to handle last-minute questions.'])}<h2>Vendor contract reminders</h2><p>Read the full agreement before paying a deposit. Confirm the exact scope, event dates and hours, taxes, overtime, staffing, travel, power requirements, meal arrangements, cancellation and postponement terms, refund rules, liability, image usage and the process for changes. Keep signed copies and receipts. Seek qualified legal advice if a term is unclear or high-risk.</p><h2>Family responsibility suggestions</h2><div class="table-wrap"><table><thead><tr><th>Area</th><th>Possible lead</th><th>What to clarify</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Ceremonies</td><td>Trusted elder + officiant contact</td><td>Sequence, items, timing and participants</td></tr><tr><td>Guest travel</td><td>Organised relative or friend</td><td>Arrivals, transport, rooms and accessibility</td></tr><tr><td>Vendor desk</td><td>Planner or non-participating family lead</td><td>Access, payments and schedule questions</td></tr><tr><td>Hospitality</td><td>Representatives from both families</td><td>Welcome, meals and guest assistance</td></tr><tr><td>Personal items</td><td>One trusted person per partner</td><td>Attire, jewellery, documents and medicines</td></tr></tbody></table></div>${ad()}${related([['wedding-budget-calculator.html','Wedding budget calculator','Build and print your estimate.'],['hindu-wedding-ceremonies.html','Hindu ceremony overview','Understand a common ceremony flow.'],['invitation-wording.html','Invitation wording','Find language that sounds like your family.']])}${faqs(planFaq)}`)}</section>`;
write('wedding-planning.html',layout({file:'wedding-planning.html',title:'Indian Wedding Planning Guide & Checklists | ShaadiGuide',desc:'Plan an Indian wedding with a 12-month timeline, milestone checklists, vendor contract reminders and practical family responsibility ideas.',h1:'Indian Wedding Planning Guide',body:`<section class="section">${planContent}`,type:'guide',schemas:[breadcrumbSchema('Wedding Planning','wedding-planning.html'),articleSchema('Indian Wedding Planning Guide','A practical planning timeline and checklists.','wedding-planning.html'),faqSchema(planFaq)]}));

const ceremonies=[['Roka','A family acknowledgement of the proposed union in some North Indian communities; format and significance vary.'],['Sagai','An engagement gathering that may include rings, gifts, blessings or family introductions.'],['Ganesh Puja','A prayer seeking blessings and the removal of obstacles, often held before wedding rituals.'],['Mehndi','Application of henna, commonly paired with music, refreshments and time with family and friends.'],['Haldi','A turmeric-based blessing ceremony observed in varied forms, often separately by each family.'],['Sangeet','A music and dance celebration; today it may range from an intimate family evening to a staged programme.'],['Baraat','The groom’s wedding procession in communities where it is observed, arriving with music and dancing.'],['Milni','A welcoming meeting of corresponding relatives from the two families in some traditions.'],['Jaimala or Varmala','An exchange of flower garlands, often symbolising mutual acceptance.'],['Kanyadaan','A ritual interpreted differently across families; some retain it, adapt its wording or choose alternatives.'],['Mangal Phera','Circling the sacred fire while making prayers or vows; number and order can vary.'],['Saptapadi','Seven steps taken together with commitments associated with married life in many traditions.'],['Sindoor','Application of vermilion as a marital symbol in communities where it is practised.'],['Mangalsutra','A sacred necklace tied or presented in several communities, with regional variations in form and meaning.'],['Vidaai','An emotional departure or transition after the ceremony, expressed differently by modern families.'],['Griha Pravesh','A welcome into the marital home, often involving blessings and symbolic entry rituals.'],['Reception','A social celebration for greeting guests, dining and congratulating the couple.']];
const cerFaq=[['Is this the order of every Hindu wedding?','No. The list is an overview, not a universal sequence. Events, names, timing and meanings vary greatly by region, sampradaya, community and family.'],['Who can explain the religious meaning for our ceremony?','Speak with the priest, pandit or officiant conducting your wedding. Ask them to explain the sequence and translations before the event so both partners can participate knowingly.'],['Can a family adapt a ceremony?','Many families discuss adaptations for time, accessibility, gender equality or personal values. Make those decisions respectfully with your partner, elders and officiant.']];
const cerBody=`<section class="section">${crumbs([['Hindu Wedding Ceremonies']])}${intro('Meaning before the moment','Hindu Wedding Ceremonies & Rituals','A respectful overview of ceremonies you may encounter before, during and after a Hindu wedding.')}<div class="notice"><strong>Traditions are not universal.</strong> Names, order, participants and interpretations vary by region, community and family. Confirm religious details with your priest, pandit, officiant or elders.</div>${article(`<h2>A flexible ceremony journey</h2><p>Some celebrations include only a few of these moments; others take place across several days. Use this overview to recognise terms, prepare questions and decide what is meaningful for your families.</p><div class="ceremony-list">${ceremonies.map(([t,d],i)=>`<section id="${t.toLowerCase().replace(/\s+|\//g,'-')}"><span>${String(i+1).padStart(2,'0')}</span><div><h3>${t}</h3><p>${d}</p>${t==='Mehndi'?'<a href="mehndi-ceremony.html">Read the Mehndi planning guide →</a>':t==='Haldi'?'<a href="haldi-ceremony.html">Read the Haldi planning guide →</a>':''}</div></section>`).join('')}</div>${ad()}<h2>Questions to ask your officiant</h2>${check(['Which rituals are essential within our family tradition?','What do the Sanskrit or regional-language verses mean?','Who participates, and where should each person sit or stand?','Which items must we arrange, and which will the officiant provide?','How long will each part take, including transitions?','How can the ceremony be explained clearly to guests?'])}${related([['haldi-ceremony.html','Haldi ceremony guide','Plan the timing, items and guest experience.'],['mehndi-ceremony.html','Mehndi ceremony guide','Prepare artists, seating and refreshments.'],['regional-weddings.html','Regional weddings','Explore how traditions differ across India.']])}${faqs(cerFaq)}`)}</section>`;
write('hindu-wedding-ceremonies.html',layout({file:'hindu-wedding-ceremonies.html',title:'Hindu Wedding Ceremonies & Rituals Guide | ShaadiGuide',desc:'A respectful overview of Hindu wedding ceremonies from Roka and Haldi to Saptapadi, Vidaai and Griha Pravesh, with cultural variation explained.',h1:'Hindu Wedding Ceremonies & Rituals',body:cerBody,type:'guide',schemas:[breadcrumbSchema('Hindu Wedding Ceremonies','hindu-wedding-ceremonies.html'),articleSchema('Hindu Wedding Ceremonies & Rituals','Overview of commonly observed Hindu wedding rituals.','hindu-wedding-ceremonies.html'),faqSchema(cerFaq)]}));

function ceremonyGuide(kind,desc,sections,faq){ const file=`${kind.toLowerCase()}-ceremony.html`; const content=`<section class="section">${crumbs([['Hindu Ceremonies','hindu-wedding-ceremonies.html'],[`${kind} Ceremony`]])}${intro('Pre-wedding celebration',`${kind} Ceremony Planning Guide`,desc)}${article(`<div class="notice"><strong>Make it your own.</strong> ${kind} customs differ by region and family. Confirm ritual details with elders and your priest, pandit or officiant.</div>${sections}${ad()}${related([['hindu-wedding-ceremonies.html','Hindu ceremony overview','See the wider wedding journey.'],[kind==='Haldi'?'mehndi-ceremony.html':'haldi-ceremony.html',kind==='Haldi'?'Mehndi guide':'Haldi guide','Plan another joyful pre-wedding event.'],['wedding-planning.html','Planning checklist','Keep the complete celebration on track.']])}${faqs(faq)}`)}</section>`; write(file,layout({file,title:`${kind} Ceremony Planning Guide | ShaadiGuide`,desc,h1:`${kind} Ceremony Planning Guide`,body:content,type:'guide',schemas:[breadcrumbSchema(`${kind} Ceremony`,file),articleSchema(`${kind} Ceremony Planning Guide`,desc,file),faqSchema(faq)]})); }
const haldiFaq=[['How long should a Haldi ceremony be?','A focused ritual may take 30 to 60 minutes, while food, music and photographs can make the gathering longer. Build the schedule around your family custom and the couple’s next commitment.'],['Can the couple have a combined Haldi?','Some couples choose a shared celebration while others hold separate events. Discuss privacy, tradition, travel and guest convenience with both families.'],['Does Haldi stain clothing?','Turmeric and oils can stain fabric and surfaces. Wear clothing you are comfortable marking, protect seating and floors, and avoid forcing paste onto anyone.']];
ceremonyGuide('Haldi','Meaning, timing, clothing, décor and a practical checklist for planning a warm and comfortable Haldi ceremony.',`<p class="article-lead">Haldi is often a joyful pause before the wedding: a time for blessings, laughter and care. Thoughtful preparation keeps the ritual comfortable and prevents a small gathering from becoming unnecessarily complicated.</p><h2>Meaning and purpose</h2><p>In many families, relatives apply a turmeric-based paste to the bride or groom while offering blessings. Meanings and recipes vary; families may associate the ritual with auspiciousness, purification, protection or preparing the skin. Treat these as family-specific interpretations, not universal claims.</p><h2>Who usually participates</h2><p>Close family members commonly begin, followed by relatives and friends if the family wishes. Decide beforehand whether children and all guests may apply Haldi, and nominate a host to guide the order gently.</p><h2>Items commonly needed</h2>${check(['Family-approved Haldi paste and small bowls','Application spoons, leaves or brushes if used','Low, stable seating with washable cushions','Floor and furniture protection','Towels, tissues, hand-washing water and waste bags','Flowers or ritual items specified by your elders or officiant','A change of clothes and private clean-up area'])}<h2>Suggested timeline</h2><div class="schedule"><div><b>Before guests arrive</b><span>Protect surfaces, test seating and prepare paste.</span></div><div><b>Welcome · 20 min</b><span>Serve a light drink and explain the flow.</span></div><div><b>Blessing ritual · 30–45 min</b><span>Invite close family first and keep application gentle.</span></div><div><b>Photos & music · 30 min</b><span>Capture group photographs without delaying clean-up.</span></div><div><b>Meal · 45–60 min</b><span>Offer easy-to-eat food while the couple freshens up.</span></div></div><h2>Clothing suggestions</h2><p>Choose breathable clothing that allows comfortable sitting and can tolerate staining. Yellow, ivory and floral looks are popular choices, not requirements. Secure dupattas, avoid delicate heirloom pieces and keep jewellery light.</p><h2>Decoration ideas</h2><p>Use marigold-inspired paper details, reusable fabric drapes, brass-toned vessels, cane baskets and fresh or fabric flowers. A cream, turmeric-yellow and leaf-green palette feels festive without crowding the space. Keep pathways clear and any floor décor away from wet areas.</p>${ad()}<h2>Food ideas</h2><p>Plan a compact menu: nimbu pani or chaas, tea, fruit, mini sandwiches or chaat served neatly, followed by one or two familiar sweets. Consider the time of day, dietary needs and whether guests will be eating with freshly washed hands.</p><h2>Photography considerations</h2><p>Ask the photographer to protect equipment, identify the best light and capture elders early. Agree on boundaries: not every guest wants turmeric on their clothes, and the couple may want a few calm portraits before the playful part begins.</p><h2>Etiquette and modern variations</h2><p>Never smear paste roughly or surprise a guest. Ask before applying it beyond hands or cheeks. Modern celebrations may be combined, kept eco-conscious, made scent-free, or shortened for accessibility. Avoid ingredients that the couple has not approved; anyone with skin concerns should make their own informed choice.</p><h2>Planning checklist</h2>${check(['Confirm the family custom, paste recipe and participants.','Choose an easy-clean space with shade or ventilation.','Send guests a note about clothing and timing.','Protect surfaces and organise wash facilities.','Confirm music, photography and food arrival times.','Prepare a calm exit and clean-up plan.'])}`,haldiFaq);
const mehndiFaq=[['How early should bridal mehndi be applied?','Many artists recommend allowing enough time for application, drying and the wedding schedule, but the right timing depends on design complexity and your artist’s aftercare guidance. Confirm it directly with your chosen artist.'],['Should every guest receive mehndi?','No. You can offer quick guest designs, book a separate artist or keep the service focused on close family. State clearly whether it is complimentary and how the queue will work.'],['What makes a mehndi space comfortable?','Supportive seating, strong neutral lighting, airflow, drinking straws, easy snacks and someone available to help the person receiving mehndi make a major difference.']];
ceremonyGuide('Mehndi','Plan a beautiful and comfortable Mehndi celebration with guidance on artists, timing, seating, lighting, food and guest designs.',`<p class="article-lead">A successful Mehndi celebration is designed around time and comfort. The central application can take hours, so seating, lighting, food and the flow of guests matter as much as décor.</p><h2>Meaning and who attends</h2><p>Mehndi refers to henna designs applied as part of pre-wedding celebration in many Indian communities. Symbolism and participation vary. The event may be an intimate afternoon with close family or a larger music-filled gathering including guests from both sides.</p><h2>Choosing a mehndi artist</h2>${check(['Review recent, unedited work in styles you genuinely like.','Ask who will attend, how many artists are included and how guest designs are priced.','Confirm expected application time, breaks, travel and overtime.','Discuss ingredients, aftercare, allergies or sensitivities directly.','Put the design scope, date, location, hours and payment terms in writing.'])}<h2>Suggested event timeline</h2><div class="schedule"><div><b>Artist setup · 30 min</b><span>Prepare lighting, seating, tables and supplies.</span></div><div><b>Bridal application</b><span>Begin at the time recommended for the design’s complexity.</span></div><div><b>Guest welcome</b><span>Open refreshments and explain guest-mehndi arrangements.</span></div><div><b>Music & photos</b><span>Keep activity near—but not crowding—the application area.</span></div><div><b>Meal service</b><span>Choose food that can be helped or eaten cleanly.</span></div></div><h2>Seating and lighting</h2><p>Provide a supportive chair with arm and back support, adjustable footrest or ottoman, cushions and a stable surface for tools. Strong, neutral lighting helps the artist see detail. Keep cables secured, provide airflow and create enough space for the artist to change position.</p><h2>Clothing</h2><p>Choose sleeves and hems that stay away from wet henna. Comfortable separates, a light lehenga, sharara or simple kurta set can work well. Put on jewellery and use the washroom before detailed application begins.</p>${ad()}<h2>Food and drinks</h2><p>Offer drinks with reusable or paper straws and small, low-mess foods that a helper can serve. Examples include fruit cups, idli bites, mini kebabs, dhokla, small wraps and bite-sized mithai. Label common allergens and provide non-spicy choices.</p><h2>Music and entertainment</h2><p>A curated playlist, acoustic performer, dholki songs or short family performances can create atmosphere. Keep speakers away from the artist and avoid a schedule that requires the person receiving mehndi to move repeatedly.</p><h2>Guest mehndi options</h2><p>Offer a limited menu of quick designs and a numbered queue, or book a dedicated guest artist. Display the service hours and likely wait. A small design station with reference cards makes choices faster.</p><h2>Planning checklist</h2>${check(['Book the artist with a written scope and timing.','Confirm comfortable seating, lighting and electricity.','Plan the bridal design before the event where possible.','Assign a helper for food, drinks and phone calls.','Choose low-mess refreshments and guest-mehndi rules.','Share practical aftercare from the artist, not internet myths.'])}`,mehndiFaq);

